    "summary": "Thiago is a senior advisor on climate change regulations and policies. He advises governments on climate finance, regulated and voluntary carbon markets, nature-based solutions and sustainable supply-chains. He also has extensive experience supporting international developmental institutions such as the World Bank, EBRD, and NEFCO in assessing options for developing and implementing carbon pricing mechanisms. Thiago has a masters degree in international public law from Edinburgh University and in international business transactions from the Catholic School of Law, Lisbon. He is also currently a PhD candidate at the UEF Law School on liability for climate and biodiversity impacts. He is fluent in English, Spanish and Portuguese.",
